// @check
// @error Unknown property `set`
// REGRESSION (B6a, C2.2): a `Set<T>` is its OWN type — it must NOT leak the `Map`
// surface. Even though a set is internally a boolean-valued `{[T]: boolean}` hash
// map, the typechecker routes set member-access to `setMemberType` (only
// `.add`/`.has`/`.delete`/`.length`/`.values`), so `.set`/`.get`/`.keys()` do NOT
// resolve. This rejects `.set` (the worst leak — it let you store an arbitrary
// boolean "value" into what should be pure membership). `.get`/`.keys()` are
// likewise gone (see sibling cases).
let s: {[string]: boolean} = Set()
s.set("a", true)
